   +--------------------------------------------------------------------+
   |                                                                    |
   |          1. Inputs - geometry, cross-section, edge length          |
   |                                                                    |
   +--------------------------------------------------------------------+

      1.1. Geometry
           * Geometric name                    : Tetrahedron
           * Geometric file type               : primitive
           * Surface type                      : closed geometry
           * The number of faces               : 4
           * The number of points              : 4
           * The number of edges               : 6

      1.2. Cross-section information
           * Section type                      : honeycomb lattice
           * The number of duplexes            : 6
           * The number of rows                : 3
           * The number of columns             : 2
           * Reference row                     : 1
           * Reference min/max column          : 1 / 2

      1.3. Edge length
           * The minimum edge length           : 42

      1.4. Design parameters
           * Junction modification             : opt
           * Vertex design                     : beveled vertex
           * Vertex modification               : mod2
           * Sticky-end for self connection    : off
           * Unpaired scffold nucleotides      : on
           * Unpaired nucleotides at vertex    : off
           * The number of bases in Tn         : depending on distance
           * Distance btw phosphate groups     : .420
           * Starting base pair ID             : 14
           * Axial rise distance [nm]          : .340
           * Radius of helix [nm]              : 1.000
           * The Gap between helixes           : .250
           * Angle of minor groove             : 150.000
           * Angle correction factor           : .000
           * Gap between two scaf xovers       : 3
           * Gap between xover(stap) and bound : 6
           * Gap between stap and scaf xovers  : 6
           * Gap between xover and first nick  : 10
           * Gap between xover and nick        : 3
           * Staple cutting method             : max
           * Non-circular stap by single xover : off
           * Minimum # of bases in scaf strand : infinite
           * Minimum # of bases in stap strand : 20
           * Midium # of bases in stap strand  : 40
           * Maximum # of bases in stap strand : 60
           * Scaffold sequence                 : user-defined sequence


   +--------------------------------------------------------------------+
   |                                                                    |
   |                2. Build modified edges and points                  |
   |                                                                    |
   +--------------------------------------------------------------------+

      2.1. Find neighboring points from initial geometry
                   1 th edge, (point 1) -> left :    3, right :    4, (point 2) -> left :    3, right :    4
                   2 th edge, (point 1) -> left :    1, right :    4, (point 2) -> left :    1, right :    4
                   3 th edge, (point 1) -> left :    2, right :    4, (point 2) -> left :    2, right :    4
                   4 th edge, (point 1) -> left :    1, right :    2, (point 2) -> left :    1, right :    2
                   5 th edge, (point 1) -> left :    3, right :    2, (point 2) -> left :    3, right :    2
                   6 th edge, (point 1) -> left :    1, right :    3, (point 2) -> left :    1, right :    3

      2.2. Find neighboring edges from initial geometry
                   1 th line, (point 1) -> left :    3, right :    5, (point 2) -> left :    2, right :    6
                   2 th line, (point 1) -> left :    1, right :    6, (point 2) -> left :    3, right :    4
                   3 th line, (point 1) -> left :    2, right :    4, (point 2) -> left :    1, right :    5
                   4 th line, (point 1) -> left :    3, right :    2, (point 2) -> left :    5, right :    6
                   5 th line, (point 1) -> left :    4, right :    6, (point 2) -> left :    3, right :    1
                   6 th line, (point 1) -> left :    5, right :    4, (point 2) -> left :    1, right :    2

      2.3. Construct arm junction data
                   1 th junc :    3-arms -> center point # :    1, lines # : (   1,    3,    5)
                   2 th junc :    3-arms -> center point # :    2, lines # : (   1,    2,    6)
                   3 th junc :    3-arms -> center point # :    3, lines # : (   2,    3,    4)
                   4 th junc :    3-arms -> center point # :    4, lines # : (   4,    5,    6)

      2.4. Set local coordinate system on initial edges
                   1 th line : t1 -> [  0.58,  0.00, -0.82 ], t2 -> [  0.82,  0.00,  0.58 ], t3 -> [  0.00, -1.00,  0.00 ]
                   2 th line : t1 -> [ -0.87,  0.50,  0.00 ], t2 -> [  0.41,  0.71, -0.58 ], t3 -> [ -0.29, -0.50, -0.82 ]
                   3 th line : t1 -> [  0.29, -0.50,  0.82 ], t2 -> [ -0.41,  0.71,  0.58 ], t3 -> [ -0.87, -0.50,  0.00 ]
                   4 th line : t1 -> [  0.00, -1.00,  0.00 ], t2 -> [ -0.82,  0.00, -0.58 ], t3 -> [  0.58,  0.00, -0.82 ]
                   5 th line : t1 -> [  0.29,  0.50,  0.82 ], t2 -> [ -0.41, -0.71,  0.58 ], t3 -> [  0.87, -0.50, -0.00 ]
                   6 th line : t1 -> [  0.87,  0.50,  0.00 ], t2 -> [  0.41, -0.71, -0.58 ], t3 -> [ -0.29,  0.50, -0.82 ]

      2.5. Seperate edges from the vertex (modified edges)
           * The number of initial points  : 4
           * The number of initial edges   : 6
           * The number of modified points : 12
           * The number of modified edges  : 6

      2.6. Update junction data with modified points
                   1 th junc :    3-arms -> mod points # : (   1,    6,   10)
                   2 th junc :    3-arms -> mod points # : (   2,    3,   12)
                   3 th junc :    3-arms -> mod points # : (   4,    5,    7)
                   4 th junc :    3-arms -> mod points # : (   8,    9,   11)

      2.7. Find the scale factor to adjust polyhedra size
           * The minumum edge length       : 42
           * Scale factor to adjust size   : .196

      2.8. Update edge length with the scale factor
                   1 th edge -> edge length :   13.600 [nm] ->   41 BP, remaining length :    0.000 [nm]
                   2 th edge -> edge length :   13.600 [nm] ->   41 BP, remaining length :    0.000 [nm]
                   3 th edge -> edge length :   13.600 [nm] ->   41 BP, remaining length :    0.000 [nm]
                   4 th edge -> edge length :   13.600 [nm] ->   41 BP, remaining length :    0.000 [nm]
                   5 th edge -> edge length :   13.600 [nm] ->   41 BP, remaining length :    0.000 [nm]
                   6 th edge -> edge length :   13.600 [nm] ->   41 BP, remaining length :    0.000 [nm]

   |                                                                    |
   |                 3. Build cross-sectional edges                     |

   +--------------------------------------------------------------------+

      3.1. Cross-section information

           * The number of duplexes         : 6

      5.4. Set strand ID on bases of the scaffold strand
           * Set strand ID into dna.base_scaf data
           * The number of scaffold strands              : 12

      5.5. Find centered scaffold crossovers
           * The number of cross-sectional edges         : 36
           * The number of sections                      : 6
           * The number of centered scaffold crossovers  : 72

      5.6.  Modify centered crossover to avoid duplicate one
           * The deleted self connecting crossovers      : 0
           * The deleted duplicate indexing crossovers   : 32
           * The number of scaffold crossovers           : 40

      5.7. Make scaffold origami
           * Build dual-graph based on closed scaffolds
               - The number of nodes in dual-graph       : 12
               - The number of edges in dual-graph       : 20
           * Generate spanning trees
           * Find the minimal spanning tree (all edge weight - 1)
               - The toal cost for this path             : 18
               - The minimal spanning tree
                 Arc    Tail node Head node   Cost
                 ---    --------- ---------   ----
                  6         1        12         1
                 10         1         2         2
                  2         2         7         1
                 11         1         4         2

           * The number of possible staple crossovers    : 122

      7.1. Write output files

   +--------------------------------------------------------------------+
   |                                                                    |
   |   8. Summary of DNA Nanostructures with Arbitrary Cross-section    |
   |                                                                    |
   +--------------------------------------------------------------------+

      8.1. Geometry, cross-section and problem description
           * Full geometric name               : 01_Tetrahedron_2cs_42bp_beveled_mod2_max
           * Geometry type                     : closed geometry
           * The number of initial faces       : 4
           * The number of initial points      : 4
           * The number of initial edges       : 6
           * The number of modified points     : 12
